usage: plugin-readme [-h] [-l {debug,info,warning,error,critical}]
                     [-a api_host] [-e e_mail] [-t api_token] [-z] [-m path]
                     [-p path] [-o path] [-r path]

Generates README from plugin.json and template

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -l {debug,info,warning,error,critical}, --log-level {debug,info,warning,error,critical}
                        Sets logging level to one of
                        debug,info,warning,error,critical. Default is logging
                        is disabled
  -a api_host, --api-host api_host
                        TrueSight Pulse API host endpoint
  -e e_mail, --email e_mail
                        e-mail that has access to the TrueSight Pulse account
  -t api_token, --api-token api_token
                        API token for given e-mail that has access to the
                        TrueSight Pulse account
  -z, --curl            Output the corresponding curl command line and exit
  -m path, --metric-manifest-path path
                        Path to metrics.json manifest. Defaults to
                        metrics.json
  -p path, --plugin-manifest-path path
                        Path to plugin.json manifest. Defaults to plugin.json
  -o path, --readme-path path
                        Path to README.md manifest. Defaults to standard out
  -r path, --readme-template-path path
                        Path to README.md template. Defaults to internal
                        template
